18:06.271 --> 18:07.954
But your sister, watch this.

18:08.514 --> 18:11.259
There's only one thing worth being concerned about.

18:11.940 --> 18:16.287
And your sister Mary, she's discovered it and will not be taken away from her.

18:16.307 --> 18:19.592
Martha, I don't want to meet love.

18:22.938 --> 18:27.486
I would have been fine if you'd have thrown some biscuits in the microwave, heated them up, slapped a little butter on them.

18:28.227 --> 18:29.629
Because I'm on my way to Jerusalem.

18:29.749 --> 18:34.898
I'm gonna give my life for the sins of human race.

18:38.082 --> 18:39.604
A bowl of Cheerios would have been fine.

18:42.567 --> 18:44.469
But you got all distracted.

18:46.071 --> 18:49.434
But your sister, from the moment I walked through the door, she sat down.

18:53.098 --> 19:00.426
She sat down and she listened to me because the reason I came is to share some thoughts.

19:00.466 --> 19:01.487
Jesus is a rabbi.

19:01.507 --> 19:04.190
Rabbi means teacher.

19:05.732 --> 19:07.794
He comes to communicate.

19:08.866 --> 19:10.728
He has things to say about life.

19:11.689 --> 19:13.090
He has things to say about reality.

19:13.811 --> 19:15.452
He had something to tell Mary.

19:15.733 --> 19:21.578
He had something to tell Martha, but she didn't get it.

19:21.638 --> 19:21.839
Why?

19:22.639 --> 19:23.280
Because she was what?

19:23.340 --> 19:25.622
She was distracted.

19:27.704 --> 19:31.708
I wonder, I wonder what some of you will miss this Christmas season.

19:33.570 --> 19:37.554
I wonder what some of you will miss hearing from Jesus.

19:38.594 --> 19:47.303
this Christmas season because you are sales and going, pain and hurt and loss and hustle and bustle.

19:48.924 --> 19:53.428
And you're not taking time to sit at the feet of Jesus to hear what he has to say.

19:55.250 --> 19:56.912
How do we avoid being distracted?

19:56.972 --> 19:58.774
How do we avoid becoming a Martha?

20:00.235 --> 20:01.737
That's the question I wanna answer today.

20:03.658 --> 20:05.580
And the answer is pretty simple.

20:06.161 --> 20:07.282
We have to realize

20:07.490 --> 20:12.957
will recognize that good things can become the wrong thing when they are prioritized over the one thing.

20:15.480 --> 20:17.342
See, it wasn't wrong to cook a meatloaf.

20:17.382 --> 20:19.105
It wasn't sinful.

20:19.125 --> 20:19.906
It wasn't evil.

20:20.446 --> 20:21.147
It was a good thing.

20:21.167 --> 20:22.809
I mean, it's a good thing to feed the Messiah.

20:22.849 --> 20:23.570
He's in your house.

20:23.590 --> 20:24.351
You can make them the best.

20:24.551 --> 20:26.113
You get your best stuff out, right?

20:26.874 --> 20:28.597
You want to give them the best service possible.

20:28.637 --> 20:29.778
This is Jesus.

20:30.082 --> 20:37.252
You don't wanna throw a few muffins in the microwave with a little butter or you wanna bring it out, get the china out.

20:39.275 --> 20:48.668
It's not wrong to do that, but good things can become the wrong things when they are prioritized over the one thing.

20:48.748 --> 20:49.810
What was the one thing?

20:49.870 --> 20:50.591
What did Jesus say?

20:51.092 --> 20:58.322
Mary has discovered the one thing and that is to sit down and listen to what I have to say.

20:58.594 --> 21:02.259
The one thing is to be with Jesus.

21:04.202 --> 21:04.943
That's what it is.

21:05.003 --> 21:07.387
That's what this whole month is about.

21:08.428 --> 21:17.342
And if you prioritize good things over the one thing, you will be distracted and you will miss out on what Jesus has to say to you this season.

21:18.984 --> 21:19.845
Just like Martha did.

21:20.787 --> 21:23.911
See, I love what Matthew says in his gospel.

21:24.993 --> 21:28.498
Matthew chapter one in his version of the Christmas story.

21:28.642 --> 21:33.569
Joseph is about to send Mary away because he finds out she's pregnant and he knows it's not his baby.

21:33.790 --> 21:34.671
You know what I'm talking about?

21:35.112 --> 21:36.754
He's like, what kind of girl is this?

21:37.755 --> 21:40.379
So he's gonna put her away, not marry her.

21:40.800 --> 21:45.427
Well, an angel comes and says, hey, Joe, this baby, this is the real deal.

21:45.727 --> 21:47.410
This baby's conceived of the Holy Spirit.

21:48.131 --> 21:55.762
And she's gonna go full term and she's gonna give birth to a boy and they're gonna name him Jesus and he's gonna save everybody from their sins.

21:56.194 --> 21:57.676
And this is the angel talking to Joseph.

21:57.716 --> 21:58.398
Go ahead and marry her.

21:58.438 --> 22:00.601
Come on, this is God's plan from the beginning of creation.

22:01.422 --> 22:09.495
And then Matthew quotes, the angel quotes Isaiah chapter seven verse 14 and Matthew chapter one verse 23.

22:09.756 --> 22:12.480
Listen to what Isaiah says.

22:13.061 --> 22:17.648
Look, the virgin will conceive a child and she'll give birth to a son and they will call his name, what?

22:18.650 --> 22:19.231
Emmanuel.

22:21.895 --> 22:23.698
Which means God with us.

22:25.250 --> 22:26.191
Like, that's Christmas.

22:28.855 --> 22:31.539
Jesus coming here to be with us.

22:31.859 --> 22:33.762
Years ago, I wanted to change the name of our church.

22:35.665 --> 22:38.408
When I became the senior pastor, I was like, man, it's so old.

22:38.448 --> 22:47.221
When Isaiah was writing, Isaiah 714, that's 500 years before Christ was born, that would make the name of our church 2,500 years old.

22:48.603 --> 22:50.686
It's like, man, it's time for a change, don't you think?

22:51.667 --> 22:51.927
You know?

22:52.268 --> 22:53.810
New pastor, new name of the church.

22:54.818 --> 22:59.846
And I thought, I can't do it because of what the name means.

23:01.248 --> 23:03.612
God with us.

23:03.812 --> 23:04.774
It's the hope.

23:04.794 --> 23:05.395
It's why we're here.

23:05.756 --> 23:06.877
It's what Christmas is all about.

23:08.921 --> 23:18.215
Now, when I say the one thing is to be with Jesus, I'm not saying that we need to sit down in a room by ourselves and look at the wall and in silence.

23:20.159 --> 23:22.322
Maybe hum.

23:25.122 --> 23:30.171
I'm talking about getting along with God and opening up his word and listening to what he has to say.

23:30.251 --> 23:38.365
I'm talking about getting with your small group and listening what God has to say through the people in your small group.

23:38.385 --> 23:40.969
I'm talking about carving out time for the one thing.

23:41.510 --> 23:49.284
And that one thing is to listen to sit down at Jesus' feet and listen to what he has to say.

23:49.324 --> 23:50.706
He's a teacher.

23:52.226 --> 24:07.122
I think that so many of us lack joy because we're not listening to what Jesus has to say about anxiety, about fear, about sexuality, about money, about parenting.

24:09.405 --> 24:13.990
Jesus has something to say about all of these issues that we go through in life.

24:14.430 --> 24:15.832
And we're not sitting down to listen.

24:17.513 --> 24:21.778
We're not hearing what he has to say and therefore we're not doing what he has to say to do, what he says to do.

24:22.114 --> 24:28.441
And then we wonder why we're stressed out and worried and anxious and popping pills to deal with our depression and all this other stuff.

24:28.461 --> 24:29.442
I'm not against medicine.

24:30.483 --> 24:32.105
I just don't think it's gonna solve our problems.

24:34.067 --> 24:38.272
I think what we have to do is listen to what he has to say and then act on what he says and then the joy comes.

24:40.574 --> 24:44.118
Jesus says to Martha, Martha, you're worried and concerned about all these details.

24:44.859 --> 24:48.543
Your sister, she chose the one thing.

24:48.583 --> 24:51.666
The best thing.

24:52.674 --> 24:56.378
and it will not be taken away from her.

24:56.398 --> 24:57.479
How do we get to this point?

24:57.800 --> 25:02.385
How did Mary know to decide to do this instead of helping her sister in the kitchen?

25:02.445 --> 25:03.666
Surely she saw her sister.

25:03.706 --> 25:05.148
Houses weren't that big back then.

25:07.491 --> 25:09.172
She sees her sister cooking the meatloaf.

25:09.193 --> 25:09.873
Nope, not gonna do it.

25:09.893 --> 25:10.574
Let's sit that and sit there.

25:10.874 --> 25:11.916
How did she get to that point?

25:13.237 --> 25:21.266
In your notes, we have to recognize the insignificance of practically everything during the Christmas season.

25:23.106 --> 25:30.076
We have to look at all this stuff, family gatherings, all the busyness, all the things that come, the trappings that come with Christmas.

25:30.376 --> 25:32.319
We have to look at them and not call them evil.

25:32.479 --> 25:33.841
I'm not a Scrooge.

25:35.483 --> 25:37.586
My wife thinks I am sometimes, but I'm not.

25:38.106 --> 25:39.328
I go to the family gatherings.

25:39.408 --> 25:43.434
I do the present stuff and sometimes I do the wrapping.

25:43.454 --> 25:52.466
But we have to recognize the insignificance of practically everything compared to Jesus coming into our house.

25:53.666 --> 25:55.288
The Apostle Paul had this mindset.

25:55.308 --> 25:59.154
In Philippians chapter three, he's writing a letter to the church of Philippi.

25:59.174 --> 26:10.410
And if you don't know who Paul is, he's this, you know, one of the main characters of the New Testament, if not the second behind Jesus, maybe Peter, had a massive trick, you know, transformation.

26:10.450 --> 26:13.234
He was a leading Jewish Pharisee.

26:14.530 --> 26:17.134
And in his former life, he had a lot of accomplishments.

26:17.174 --> 26:18.756
He was born from the right family.

26:18.776 --> 26:20.118
He had the right education.

26:20.259 --> 26:21.500
He had all the accolades.

26:21.581 --> 26:23.303
He was like a master of the law.

26:24.245 --> 26:32.838
And in Philippians chapter three, he writes these statements that I think capture Mary's heart and what helped her to make this decision to sit at Jesus' feet.

26:33.138 --> 26:35.261
He said, Paul says, I once thought these things were valuable.

26:35.281 --> 26:35.662
What things?

26:35.782 --> 26:39.548
All of my accomplishments before I met Christ, they were valuable to me.

26:39.908 --> 26:41.130
But now I consider them what?

26:41.230 --> 26:42.712
Say with me, worthless.

26:42.732 --> 26:43.794
They're insignificant.

26:43.938 --> 26:45.240
because of what Christ has done.

26:45.300 --> 26:46.461
He goes on and he says this.

26:47.222 --> 26:56.935
Yes, everything else is worthless when compared to the infinite value of knowing Christ Jesus my Lord.

26:56.955 --> 27:08.050
And he presses in even harder and he says this, for his sake I have discarded, I've gotten rid of, I've thrown it in a trash, everything else counting it as garbage or dung or refuse.

27:09.122 --> 27:11.544
so that I could gain Christ and be found with him.

27:11.564 --> 27:12.886
In other words, here's Mary's heart.

27:13.306 --> 27:27.820
Jesus walks into the house and all of the other things that were good things became insignificant things because she saw the most important thing, which was to sit down at Jesus' feet and listen to what he has to say.

27:29.041 --> 27:30.323
Food is very important.

27:31.143 --> 27:34.126
It's not evil, it's not wrong, we have to eat if we don't eat, we die.

27:34.487 --> 27:37.970
But in that moment, Mary says, that's insignificant, we'll eat tomorrow.

27:39.106 --> 27:40.488
We'll eat when Jesus leaves.

27:41.349 --> 27:42.691
We'll cook a meal tomorrow.

27:42.971 --> 27:46.095
Right now, the most important thing is to sit down and be with him.

27:46.115 --> 27:48.558
That's the whole purpose of his coming.

27:49.580 --> 27:50.241
He's a teacher.

27:50.301 --> 27:51.602
He's a rabbi.

27:51.642 --> 27:52.383
He's the savior.

27:52.484 --> 27:53.945
He is the Lord.

27:54.446 --> 27:56.569
What if that was our attitude during the Christmas season?

27:58.451 --> 28:02.236
What if our attitude was the same as the psalmist in Psalm 73 verse 25?

28:02.837 --> 28:05.380
Lord, I just desire you more than anything on earth.

28:05.460 --> 28:06.642
I know it's Christmas time.

28:08.162 --> 28:12.828
I know there's gonna be some fun festivities, and there's gonna be some family times, and then he's gonna decorate.

28:12.909 --> 28:17.054
I know there's gonna be some, but I desire you more than anything on this earth.

28:17.435 --> 28:19.077
What if that was your heart during Christmas time?

28:20.259 --> 28:21.020
Wow.

28:21.040 --> 28:22.822
Here's what I would imagine would happen.

28:24.665 --> 28:32.275
You would listen to him more, you would sit down, you would choose the one thing, and you'd become more aware of him.

28:32.295 --> 28:37.202
Because remember, attention leads to awareness, and awareness opens up the door for

28:37.602 --> 28:38.203
for joy.

28:38.223 --> 28:50.338
So something tells me that this Christmas season, you will experience more joy, which is the purpose of Christmas.

28:53.041 --> 28:55.664
So my question to you today, my challenge to you today is a simple one.

28:57.026 --> 28:58.488
How will you prioritize the one thing?

29:01.071 --> 29:02.112
How will you prioritize?

29:02.172 --> 29:03.474
How will you do what Mary did?

29:05.602 --> 29:06.724
I'll tell you what I do.

29:06.884 --> 29:10.008
I mean, I do it every day anyway, but especially during the Christmas season.

29:10.409 --> 29:11.550
This is my journal right here.

29:13.513 --> 29:15.776
I open this up every morning, did it again this morning.

29:17.078 --> 29:25.349
And I have my Bible and I have a spot at my house, and I open it up, and I read through the one-year New Testament, usually around six o'clock, 5'36 o'clock.

29:25.389 --> 29:31.097
And as I'm reading through the New Testament, Old Testament New Testament, I just ask God, show me something.

29:31.498 --> 29:32.359
What do you want to say to me?

29:32.379 --> 29:32.680
I'm here.

29:33.701 --> 29:34.482
You're the teacher.

29:34.850 --> 29:39.096
I'm the student, and I just write down some things he shows me.

29:42.340 --> 29:43.982
Every day, just not much.

29:45.044 --> 29:47.387
I'll just jot down a few thoughts about one page a day.

29:48.649 --> 29:52.013
And I hear his voice, and then I try to do what he says.

29:54.436 --> 29:56.039
And I know for some of you, that's hard.

29:57.260 --> 29:58.582
It's a hard discipline to create.

29:59.984 --> 30:04.530
But you forfeit joy without it.

30:05.826 --> 30:09.389
without spending that time with God, hearing Him, listening to Him.

30:10.390 --> 30:12.672
So maybe we'll incorporate that.

30:12.712 --> 30:15.395
Maybe you've fallen away from a devotional time or time with God.

30:15.435 --> 30:21.821
Maybe during the month of December, during this TIS, the season series, you prioritize the one thing.

30:22.762 --> 30:24.083
Maybe you let some other things go.

30:24.123 --> 30:25.865
Maybe you do less of some other things.

30:25.905 --> 30:27.126
Maybe you do less social media.

30:27.146 --> 30:30.950
Did you know the average person has two hours and 23 minutes on social media every day?

30:31.810 --> 30:33.632
So you really can't say, well, I don't have time.

30:34.373 --> 30:35.634
That's a joke.

30:35.810 --> 30:41.197
You know, we binge watch Netflix and then we say, I don't have time to spend with Jesus.

30:41.357 --> 30:43.900
I mean, it's a joke, come on, come on, seriously.

30:44.741 --> 30:46.363
How many shows have you watched on Netflix?

30:46.423 --> 30:48.466
It's like, I don't have time to spend with Jesus, really.

30:49.848 --> 30:51.310
You gotta get serious with yourself.

30:52.491 --> 30:53.813
I'm not saying those things are wrong.

30:54.614 --> 30:55.996
You know, we watch Netflix, that's fine.

30:57.377 --> 30:58.779
We've watched Stranger Things, okay.

30:59.560 --> 31:01.042
Not a huge fan, but I liked it.

31:02.242 --> 31:04.444
I'm not saying those things are wrong, but here's what happens.

31:04.624 --> 31:11.711
When we prioritize good things over wrong things, I'm sorry, when we prioritize good things over the best thing, they become the wrong things.

31:13.113 --> 31:14.174
And we become distracted.

31:15.175 --> 31:16.836
So how will you prioritize?

31:16.957 --> 31:20.480
Maybe it's something as simple as shifting the way you listen to it musically.

31:20.520 --> 31:23.643
Maybe you make a playlist of worship music during this Christmas season.

31:24.364 --> 31:29.269
You shift a little bit away from Christmas music and more towards worship music so that you can kindle a love for God.

31:29.669 --> 31:30.610
I don't know how you do it.

31:31.682 --> 31:43.523
But I would challenge you to prioritize the one thing over all of the other details so that you can pay attention, so that you can be create awareness, so that you can open up the opportunity for joy.

31:45.627 --> 31:46.208
Fair challenge.

31:47.370 --> 31:50.996
Now, as we wrap up today, I want to go back to the Gospel of Matthew.

31:52.559 --> 31:56.626
I want to go back to that moment where Joseph was going to privately

31:57.026 --> 32:01.911
put Mary away and break off the engagement because he found out she was pregnant.

32:03.252 --> 32:05.614
And the angel comes to him and says, no, no, no, don't do it.

32:07.015 --> 32:10.659
This baby inside of Mary is conceived of the Holy Spirit.

32:12.040 --> 32:13.601
And I already mentioned this, but I'll mention it again.

32:13.682 --> 32:17.505
This is what the angel said to Joseph in verse 21 of Matthew chapter one.

32:19.227 --> 32:21.769
And she'll have a son and you are to name him Jesus.

32:23.511 --> 32:25.012
And here's the mission of Christmas, ready?

32:25.653 --> 32:26.994
This is the source of our joy.

32:27.778 --> 32:30.162
for he will save his people from their sins.

32:32.184 --> 32:33.987
He is the Savior.

32:34.067 --> 32:35.690
He is the deliverer, from what?

32:35.990 --> 32:38.874
From the penalty of sin, from the power of sin?

32:42.019 --> 32:43.661
God and man reconciled.

32:43.681 --> 32:45.284
We just got done saying that a few minutes ago.

32:45.364 --> 32:49.610
How is God and man reconciled through Christ Jesus, through his death on the cross?

32:50.251 --> 32:57.682
He paid the penalty for my sin, for your sin, for the sin of the whole world, so that you can experience fellowship with God, so that you can experience joy.

32:58.370 --> 33:01.035
the joy of knowing God.

33:01.857 --> 33:03.621
And some of you need to step into that today.

33:04.943 --> 33:07.108
Some of you need to begin a relationship with God today.

33:07.649 --> 33:10.915
Some of you need to be saved from your sins.

33:11.958 --> 33:18.130
I'm not talking about becoming a religious person or joining a church or being confirmed or being baptized.

33:19.618 --> 33:20.459
or anything like that.

33:20.539 --> 33:22.841
I'm not talking about anything about religion.

33:22.901 --> 33:28.066
I'm talking about looking at God, looking at Jesus saying, will you forgive me of my sins?

33:28.407 --> 33:31.129
I trust that you died on the cross for me.

33:31.189 --> 33:37.355
And you came back to life to wipe away the penalty of sin held against me.

33:37.415 --> 33:38.937
I trust you.

33:41.059 --> 33:42.120
That's not joining a religion.

33:42.921 --> 33:43.982
That's not joining a church.

33:44.642 --> 33:46.324
That is becoming a Christ follower.

33:46.344 --> 33:48.306
That is receiving eternal life.

33:48.802 --> 33:49.963
and the forgiveness of sins.

33:50.224 --> 33:55.669
And if that's what you'd like to do right now, if you feel drawn into this moment, I'm gonna say a simple prayer, it's a prayer of faith.

33:55.709 --> 34:05.460
Take these words, make them your own, and you'll become a Christ follower today, and you'll begin to experience the purpose of Christmas, which is joy.

34:05.860 --> 34:07.102
If you feel led, will you pray with me?

34:12.367 --> 34:18.514
Dear Jesus, I believe you died in the cross for me.

34:21.698 --> 34:35.717
gave your life to pay for my sin, to save me, to deliver me from the penalty of sin.

34:37.780 --> 34:43.828
And so I reach out in faith, and I trust you.

34:45.931 --> 34:51.378
I ask you to wash me, cleanse me, and forgive me.

34:52.482 --> 34:54.545
of all that I've done wrong.

34:58.651 --> 35:00.032
I place my life in your hands.

35:02.876 --> 35:03.958
Thank you for your grace.

35:05.961 --> 35:07.463
Thank you for your mercy.

35:10.907 --> 35:14.993
Fill my life now with joy.

35:17.216 --> 35:18.238
The joy of knowing you.

35:20.380 --> 35:21.522
I pray this in Christ's name.

35:22.786 --> 35:25.449
Everybody said, amen, amen.

35:25.489 --> 35:27.511
Can we give God glory today, church, amen?

35:33.158 --> 35:40.025
You know, when I did that, when I made that decision many, many years ago, when I was 17, I had someone come alongside of me.

35:40.586 --> 35:41.547
His name was Byron.

35:42.608 --> 35:46.513
And he was a man at this church I went to.

35:46.533 --> 35:51.218
He just walked up to me and he said, hey, now that you've put your faith in Christ,

35:51.746 --> 35:57.134
I want you to begin reading the Bible and studying it and memorizing key passages.

35:57.194 --> 36:00.379
And at that time, you know, this guy looked like Moses to me.

36:00.439 --> 36:02.762
He was a retired missionary from Africa.

36:02.782 --> 36:03.723
He had white hair.

36:03.763 --> 36:07.228
I thought, if Moses were alive today, this would be this guy.

36:07.789 --> 36:09.952
And so, you know, I'm like a teenager.

36:10.533 --> 36:12.116
And so I'm like, absolutely.

36:12.396 --> 36:13.097
Where should I start?

36:13.117 --> 36:16.882
He gave me a couple of passages to start in and I memorized those passages.

36:16.983 --> 36:19.346
And I never lost my

36:19.618 --> 36:22.407
appetite for taking God's word in.

36:22.447 --> 36:33.522
And so that's why as a church anytime someone trusts Christ as their Savior, we want to immediately, immediately put a New Testament in your hand so that you can begin reading it and memorizing key passages

36:33.634 --> 36:38.983
so that you can grow in your faith, understand God's will, and begin to understand how God wants to change you from the inside out.

36:39.043 --> 36:41.688
So if you trusted Christ today, grab one of these in the way out.

36:41.728 --> 36:44.212
It's your campus in the back of the auditorium there.

36:44.232 --> 36:47.217
If you did it online, there's a place there that you can fill out some information.

36:47.598 --> 36:49.761
We'll send one of them to you in the mail.

36:50.082 --> 36:52.626
So one more time, can we give God glory, amen?

